In your manual test, did you observe the docker stop time reduced? Do you have test result?

> In your manual test, did you observe the docker stop time reduced? Do you have test result?

@qiluo-msft With many rounds of manual testing, I am not able to verify that these changes reduce docker stop time. 

Test results:

Without change: 

`time docker stop telemetry`

Average run:

real    0m3.229s
user    0m0.017s
sys     0m0.013s

With change:

`time docker stop telemetry`

Average run:

real    0m3.036s
user    0m0.027s
sys     0m0.025s

Both runs (with and without changes) have a docker stop time of ~3s on average, some runs one or the other might produce a higher number, no consistent proof that these changes reduce docker stop time.
